          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  The angular dependence of the 417 keV line was",
                "fitted as Legendre polynomial and the attenuation",
                "coefficients which have been analytically calculated",
                "from the experimental setup geometry (see A.J.Ferguson,",
                " 'Angular Correlation Methods in Gamma-Ray",
                "Spectroscopy' (North-Holland, Amsterdam, 1965)).",
                "The total cr.section is given as 4 x Pi x A0.",
                "Data were measured at 90, 112.5, 135 and 157.5 deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-supported Mg-24 targets were used. The thicknesses",
                "of the targets ranged from 0.5 to 17.7 mg/cm2",
                "All Mg-24 targets were enriched more than 99%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE",
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma rays were detected with four large",
                "volume HP-Ge detectors. The Ge crystals were surrounded",
                "by bismuth germinate(BGO) detectors for Compton",
                "suppression.",
                "The detectors efficiencies were determined using",
                "calibrated radioactive sources (60Co,88Y,137Cs,152Eu)",
                "and proton-induced reactions for which gamma-production",
                "cross sections are known:",
                " 24Mg(p,p')24Mg (Egamma = 1.37 MeV) and 16O(p,p')16O",
                " (Egamma = 2.74 and 6.13 MeV)."
              ]
            }
          ],
